<refentry id="bif.Assign" xreflabel="Assign">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>Assign</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>Assign</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>Assign</refname>
<refpurpose>
Sets the value of a variable
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
Assign[name->TEXT, value->T*] =: T
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>

<function>Assign</function> creates a new variable
<parameter>name</parameter>, with value <parameter>value</parameter>.
Returns the value assigned.  If <parameter>name</parameter> is already a 
defined
variable in the current scope, then if it is of type <type>T</type>, it is
modified to have return value of <parameter>value</parameter>.  If it is of a
different type, an error results.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>Short form</title>
<para>
<literal>x := value</literal>
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>See also</title>
<para>
<xref linkend="bif.Clear">, <xref linkend="bif.UnAssign">.
</para>
</refsect1>

</refentry>



